Defendant JaJuan Q. Shaw in court with attorney Thomas E. Hayes.  Defendant JaJuan Q. Shaw in custody.  
Cynthia M. Davis appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, defense and defendant. 
 
COUNT 1:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 42 MONTHS, CONCURRENT to sentence currently being served with credit for 0 days. 
The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 18 MONTHS.  
The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 24 MONTHS.

The defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.  

The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 4 YEARS with the following conditions.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:/EXTENDED SUPERVISON (if revoked):
*Serve 12 Months in the House of Correction with release for employment and treatment;
*Obtain AODA assessment and complete follow-up care/treatment;
*Absolute sobriety- cooperate with random urine screens;
*No illegal drug dealing or association with drug community (drug users/dealers/houses);
*Cooperate with all rules deemed appropriate by department of corrections;
* No contact with victim N.G. or her residence or her family;
*Provide DNA sample- pay surcharge;
*Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs by the end of probation period- any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment;

Defendant is informed he may not possess and/or own any firearms.  Defendant is informed he may not vote in any election until his/her civil rights have been reinstated.  Defendant advised of right to appeal this sentence.  The Court finds that expungement would not be against public interest IF each and every condition of probation is completed including costs, fees, surcharges, and assessments.
Filed;
